&reftitle.description;

 boolimagewebp
 GdImageimage
 resourcestringnullfile&null;
 intquality-1



 Outputs or saves a WebP version of the given image.

  &reftitle.parameters;



    &gd.image.description;

     file


&gd.image.path;



     quality



       quality ranges from 0 (worst
       quality, smaller file) to 100 (best quality, biggest file).

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.4.0

     Now throws a ValueError if quality is invalid.


   &gd.changelog.image-param;

  &reftitle.examples;



    Saving an WebP file


<?php
// Create a blank image and add some text
$im = imagecreatetruecolor(120, 20);
$text_color = imagecolorallocate($im, 233, 14, 91);

imagestring($im, 1, 5, 5,  'WebP with PHP', $text_color);

// Save the image
imagewebp($im, 'php.webp');
?>
